Plot Generation

Data visualization for gardener manuscript.

# Import libraries
library(tidyverse)
library(ggeffects)
library(see)
library(lme4)
library(lmerTest)
library(cowplot)
# Get data
load('~/Documents/UofT/Projects/MackLab/All_Analysis.RData')

# Recode the data to make things easier
df_clean$Type <- recode_factor(df_clean$Type,
                               'Prototype'='prototype',
                               'RuleFollowing'='rule-follower',
                               'Exception'='exception')
df_clean$Type <- factor(df_clean$Type,
                        levels=c('prototype','rule-follower','exception'))

df_clean$Condition <- recode_factor(df_clean$Condition,
                                    'Early'='early','Late'='delayed')


generaltheme <- theme(axis.line=element_line(linewidth=0.5,colour='black'),
                      axis.ticks=element_line(size=0.5,colour='black'),
                      axis.title=element_text(size=9,colour='black'),
                      axis.text=element_text(size=7,colour='black'))
# visualize accuracy over time
df_bin <- df_clean %>% 
  filter(Block=='Learn') %>% #,Count<=36) %>% 
  mutate(CountBin=floor((Count-1)/12)+1) %>% 
  group_by(Participant,Type,Condition,CountBin) %>% 
  summarise(acc=mean(Learn_Corr))
`summarise()` has grouped output by 'Participant', 'Type', 'Condition'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.
pd <- position_dodge(0.8)

ggplot(df_bin,aes(x=CountBin,y=acc,colour=Type,linetype=Condition,shape=Condition,
                  group=interaction(Condition,Type)))+
  geom_hline(yintercept=0.5,colour='black',linetype='dotted',linewidth=0.25)+
  geom_point(position=pd,alpha=0.15,size=1.5,shape=16,stroke=0)+
  stat_summary(fun='mean',geom='line',position=pd)+
  stat_summary(fun.data='mean_cl_boot',geom='point',shape=16,size=3,colour='white',
               fill='white',position=pd,show.legend=F)+
  stat_summary(fun.data='mean_cl_boot',position=pd)+
  scale_colour_viridis_d(option='plasma',begin=0.2,end=0.7)+
  scale_shape_manual(values=c(19,1))+
  scale_linetype_manual(values=c('solid','longdash'))+
  scale_x_continuous(breaks=c(1,2,3,4,5,6))+
  guides(colour=guide_legend(order=1))+
  coord_cartesian(ylim=c(0,1))+
  theme_classic()+
  theme(strip.background=element_blank())+
  generaltheme+
  theme(legend.position='top',legend.direction='vertical',
        legend.box='horizontal',legend.spacing=unit(0,'pt'),
        legend.title=element_blank())+
  labs(x='repetition block',y='learning accuracy')


# accuracy over trials ---------------------------------------------------------

df_bin_trial <- df_clean %>% 
  filter(Block=='Learn') %>% 
  mutate(All_Trial=(as.numeric(Learn_Block)-1)*48+Learn_Trial) %>% 
  mutate(TrialBin=floor(All_Trial/48)+1) %>% 
  group_by(Participant,Type,Condition,TrialBin) %>% 
  summarise(acc=mean(Learn_Corr),n=length(Learn_Corr))
`summarise()` has grouped output by 'Participant', 'Type', 'Condition'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.
ggplot(df_bin_trial,
       aes(x=TrialBin,y=acc,colour=Type,linetype=Condition,shape=Condition,
           group=interaction(Condition,Type)))+
  geom_hline(yintercept=0.5,colour='black',linetype='dotted',size=0.25)+
  geom_point(position=pd,alpha=0.1,size=2.5,shape=16,stroke=0)+
  stat_summary(fun='mean',geom='line',position=pd)+
  stat_summary(fun.data='mean_cl_boot',geom='point',shape=16,size=3,colour='white',
               fill='white',position=pd,show.legend=F)+
  stat_summary(fun.data='mean_cl_boot',position=pd)+
  scale_colour_viridis_d(option='plasma',begin=0.2,end=0.7)+
  scale_linetype_manual(values=c('solid','longdash'))+
  scale_shape_manual(values=c(19,1))+
  scale_x_continuous(breaks=c(1,2,3))+
  guides(colour=guide_legend(order=1))+
  coord_cartesian(ylim=c(0,1))+
  theme_classic()+
  theme(strip.background=element_blank())+
  generaltheme+
  theme(legend.position='top',legend.direction='vertical',
        legend.box='horizontal',legend.spacing=unit(0,'pt'),
        legend.title=element_blank())+
  labs(x='trial block',y='learning accuracy')

df_nf <- df_clean %>% 
  filter(Block=='NF') %>% 
  group_by(Participant,Type,Condition) %>% 
  summarise(acc=mean(NF_Corr))
`summarise()` has grouped output by 'Participant', 'Type'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.
pd2 <- position_dodge(0.4)
ggplot(df_nf,aes(x=Type,y=acc,colour=Type,shape=Condition,group=Condition))+
  geom_point(position=pd2,size=2.5,alpha=0.1,shape=16,stroke=0)+
  stat_summary(fun.data='mean_cl_boot',geom='point',fill='white',
               colour='white',shape=19,position=pd2,show.legend=F)+
  stat_summary(fun.data='mean_cl_boot',position=pd2,size=0.5)+
  scale_colour_viridis_d(option='plasma',begin=0.2,end=0.7,guide='none')+
  scale_shape_manual(values=c(19,1))+
  coord_cartesian(ylim=c(0,1))+
  theme_classic()+generaltheme+
  theme(legend.position='top',legend.title=element_blank())+
  labs(x='',y='test accuracy')

# Combined learning and test blocks
df_all <- rbind(df_bin_trial,
                df_nf %>% mutate(TrialBin=4,n=8))
ggplot(df_all,
       aes(x=TrialBin,y=acc,colour=Type,linetype=Condition,shape=Condition,
           group=interaction(Condition,Type)))+
  geom_hline(yintercept=0.5,colour='black',linetype='dotted',size=0.25)+
  geom_point(position=pd,alpha=0.1,size=1.5,shape=16,stroke=0)+
  stat_summary(data=filter(df_all,TrialBin<=3),
               fun='mean',geom='line',position=pd)+
  stat_summary(fun.data='mean_cl_boot',geom='point',shape=16,size=3,colour='white',
               fill='white',position=pd,show.legend=F)+
  stat_summary(fun.data='mean_cl_boot',position=pd)+
  scale_colour_viridis_d(option='plasma',begin=0.2,end=0.7)+
  scale_linetype_manual(values=c('solid','longdash'))+
  scale_shape_manual(values=c(19,1))+
  scale_x_continuous(breaks=c(1,2,3,4),labels=c(1,2,3,'test'))+
  guides(colour=guide_legend(order=1))+
  coord_cartesian(ylim=c(0,1))+
  ggtitle(" ")+
  theme_classic()+
  theme(strip.background=element_blank())+
  generaltheme+
  theme(legend.position='top',legend.direction='vertical',
        legend.box='horizontal',legend.spacing=unit(0,'pt'),
        legend.title=element_blank())+
  labs(x='trial block',y='accuracy')
